  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Helping Disaster-stricken Kumamoto by Kitchen Cars</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Kumamoto Earthquake, still 20,559 people are in emergency shelters. Food poisoning under hot weather is now a serious issue. The Kamaishi Kitchen Car Project (KKCP) certified by the health authority, returning to Tohoku Tsunami supports and responding to community-level requests of their know-how, is sending two kitchen cars to serve 10,000 people in diverse shelters. This also is a part of new efforts to build  the Kitchen-car Disaster Support Network in Japan.</narrative>
  </description>
